<h1>Spaghetti Casserole</h1>
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
<li>1 pound spaghetti, cooked</li>
<li>1 pound ground beef</li>
<li>2 24-ounce jars marinara sauce</li>
<li>4 tablespoons butter, cut into 8 slices</li>
<li>8 ounces cottage cheese</li>
<li>8 ounces sour cream</li>
<li>8 ounces cream cheese</li>
<li>1/2 cup (2 ounces) shredded sharp cheddar cheese</li>
</ul>
<h2>Steps</h2>
<ol>
<li>Brown the ground beef in a pan over medium heat, then add marinara sauce and mix well. Set aside.</li>
<li>In a large bowl, combine the cottage cheese, sour cream, and cream cheese until smooth.</li>
<li>Preheat oven to 350Â°F.</li>
<li>Place slices of butter at the bottom of a 9x13-inch casserole dish.</li>
<li>Add half of the cooked spaghetti.</li>
<li>Spread half of the cheese mixture evenly over the spaghetti.</li>
<li>Layer half of the meat sauce over the cheese mixture.</li>
<li>Add the remaining spaghetti, then spread the remaining cheese mixture over the spaghetti, and top with the rest of the meat sauce.</li>
<li>Bake for 30 minutes.</li>
<li>Sprinkle shredded cheddar cheese on top and bake for an additional 15 minutes.</li>
<li>Serve with garlic bread and a side of veggies!</li>
</ol>
